The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, February 04, 2004 				 Cop arrested for foul play in riot case
 OUR CORRESPONDENT  Ahmedabad, Feb. 3: The  CBI has arrested a head constable on the charge of tampering  with evidence of the Randhikpur rape and massacre that occurred  during the Gujarat riots.																								Narpat Patel, posted in Dahod district, was sent to CBI custody for eight days by the district magistrates court in Ahmedabad. He was in charge of the Randhikpur outpost when 14 people were massacred.																								A survivor was Bilkis Bano, who along with her relatives was fleeing their village when a mob set upon them. The women were gangraped before being killed along with the men and children. Patel, as the investigating officer, had handled the Bilkis Bano case.																								Bilkis Bano claimed to have seen 14 bodies after the incident. Patel, arrested this morning, claimed to have seen and buried only seven. Bilkis Bano delivers																								Bilkis Bano, allegedly gangraped during the Gujarat riots, delivered a daughter at a hospital in Godhra on Sunday, her husband Yaqoob told PTI today.
